    public static class Object2DoubleSortedMaps.Singleton<K>
extends Object2DoubleMaps.Singleton<K>
implements Object2DoubleSortedMap<K>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    An immutable class representing a type-specific singleton sorted map.

    This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific sorted map.

      • object2DoubleEntrySet

        public ObjectSortedSet<Object2DoubleMap.Entry<K>> object2DoubleEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Object2DoubleMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Object2DoubleMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        object2DoubleEntrySet in interface Object2DoubleMap<K>
